{"questionId":"14474","questionHtml":"<p>Given that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"z\">\n  <mi>z</mi>\n</math></span> &gt; −1.6, find the probability that z &lt; 2.4 . Write your answer in terms of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {z >&nbsp; - 1.6} \\right) = 1 - a\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>z</mi>\n      <mo>&gt;</mo>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1.6</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;(seen anywhere) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>recognizing conditional probability&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg&nbsp; &nbsp;</em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {A\\left| B \\right.} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>A</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>|</mo>\n        <mi>B</mi>\n        <mo fence=\"true\" stretchy=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\"></mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {B\\left| A \\right.} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>B</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>|</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo fence=\"true\" stretchy=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\"></mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>correct working&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{P}}\\left( {z < 2.4 \\cap z >&nbsp; - 1.6} \\right)}}{{{\\text{P}}\\left( {z >&nbsp; - 1.6} \\right)}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>P</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>z</mi>\n          <mo>&lt;</mo>\n          <mn>2.4</mn>\n          <mo>∩</mo>\n          <mi>z</mi>\n          <mo>&gt;</mo>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>1.6</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>P</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>z</mi>\n          <mo>&gt;</mo>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>1.6</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>,&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{P}}\\left( { - 1.6 < z < 2.4} \\right)}}{{{\\text{P}}\\left( {z >&nbsp; - 1.6} \\right)}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>P</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>1.6</mn>\n          <mo>&lt;</mo>\n          <mi>z</mi>\n          <mo>&lt;</mo>\n          <mn>2.4</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>P</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>z</mi>\n          <mo>&gt;</mo>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>1.6</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {z < 2.4\\left| z \\right. >&nbsp; - 1.6} \\right) = \\frac{{1 - a - b}}{{1 - a}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>z</mi>\n      <mo>&lt;</mo>\n      <mn>2.4</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>|</mo>\n        <mi>z</mi>\n        <mo fence=\"true\" stretchy=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\"></mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>&gt;</mo>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1.6</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp; N4</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award the final <em><strong>A1</strong></em> if correct answer is seen followed by incorrect simplification.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14474","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ1.S_9b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Given that z > −1.6, find the probability that z < 2.4 . Write your answer in terms of a and b .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}